{"id":91469,"title":"[Surgical treatment of the injured persons for closed coexistent abdominal injuries depending on the trauma severity].","abstract":"The results of surgical treatment of 232 injured persons, suffering closed abdominal trauma, were analyzed. In 117 injured persons a standard surgical tactic was applied, and in 115--the improved one the treatment-diagnostic tactic, what have had permitted to reduce the complications occurrence rate from 62.4 to 54.8%, total lethality--from 35.0 to 27.8%.","date":"2014-02-07","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24502015","annotations":[{"name":"Trauma (medicine)","weight":0.705743,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trauma_(medicine)"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.622654,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Abdomen","weight":0.460335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdomen"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.266588,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.25078,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Blunt trauma","weight":0.0494293,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blunt_trauma"},{"name":"Abdominal trauma","weight":0.0486346,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdominal_trauma"},{"name":"Suffering","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suffering"},{"name":"Standardization","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standardization"},{"name":"Military tactics","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military_tactics"}]}
